 the doorway stood his father.

'Go to your room,' he said, glancing briefly at his son. Luzhin, who was being sent out of a room for the first time in his life, remained as he was on his knees out of sheer astonishment. 'Did you hear?' said his father, Luzhin flushed and began to look for the fallen pieces on the carpet. 'Hurry up,' said his father in a thunderous voice such as he had never used before. His aunt hastily began to put the pieces any which way into their box. Her hands trembled. O